"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The np.insert function is being used incorrectly in this context. The insert operation is modifying the shape of the array along the specified axis, which can lead to inconsistencies when trying to assign the result back to arr[i]. The shape of arr[i] is (4,) and after the insert operation, it becomes (5,), which causes a shape mismatch error.\", \"patch\": \"6c6\\n< arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3)\\n---\\n> arr = np.insert(arr, 1, 3, axis=1)\"}"